        "id": 2190719,
        "name": "Mark Golodetz",
        "username": "Mark_Golodetz",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/mark_golodetz/{size}/76850_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-05-29T15:13:40.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I remember going to Nashville for a large Petrus vertical, and the night before we went to Tom Black\u2019s house and he served some interesting wines from his cellar. The highlight not only of the evening, but also the whole weekend was a magnificent bottle of Leroy Auxey. Perfect, balanced and fragrant with a finish that went on for several minutes.</p>\n<p>There were some great bottles of Petrus the following day, but it\u2019s that incredible bottle of Auxey, which should not have been so incredible, that stands out for me.</p>",
