      {
        "id": 2191649,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-05-31T10:52:31.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This sounds terrific. It was a great vintage. Rousseau\u2019s '64 Gevrey village is still drinking well, though similarly coming towards the end of its plateau. And a Gevrey village from a n\u00e9goce called Allier was excellent last month too\u2014frankly as good as Rousseau\u2019s. I suspect these older village bottlings often contained wine from less famous 1er crus. After all, how often has anyone seen, say, 1964 Gevrey Cherbaudes or Petite Chapelle?</p>\n<p>As for the potential of Auxey\u2026 Maison Leroy is not established in Auxey by accident!</p>",
